      • UploadFailedEvent

        public UploadFailedEvent(java.lang.String uuid,
                         java.lang.String nodeId,
                         boolean willRetry,
                         int retryTime,
                         int numberOfAttempt)
        Creates a new UploadFailedEvent.
        Parameters:
        uuid - The uuid of the file that failed to upload.
        nodeId - The id of the node for which the upload failed.
        willRetry - If set to true, this means that the framework will retry the upload by itself later on (mostly after all other files are done).
        retryTime - The time in seconds, after which we will retry.
        numberOfAttempt - The number of the next attempt.
